title: Occasional bandwidth test failures, timeout in ServerFixture

content.raw:
We're having several intermittent failures of the bandwidth test.

* [gazebo_1.5 #15 bandwidth](http://build.osrfoundation.org/job/gazebo-gazebo_1.5-devel-precise-amd64/15/console)
* [gazebo_1.5 #17 bandwidth](http://build.osrfoundation.org/job/gazebo-gazebo_1.5-devel-precise-amd64/17/console)
* [gazebo_default #242 bandwidth](http://build.osrfoundation.org/job/gazebo-default-devel-precise-amd64/242/console)

The tests start but fail to load the server within the 30 second timeout specified in [ServerFixture:130-136](#!/osrf/gazebo/src/2ed06f79d13f07666115e722cdfd8db82f099fd0/test/ServerFixture.hh#cl-130)
~~~
69: [==========] Running 1 test from 1 test case.
69: [----------] Global test environment set-up.
69: [----------] 1 test from BandwidthTest
69: [ RUN      ] BandwidthTest.Bandwidth
69: Gazebo multi-robot simulator, version 1.5.0
69: Copyright (C) 2013 Open Source Robotics Foundation.
69: Released under the Apache 2 License.
69: http://gazebosim.org
69: 
69: [1;33mWarning [ModelDatabase.cc:295][0m Getting models from[http://gazebosim.org/models/]. This may take a few seconds.
69: /var/lib/jenkins/workspace/gazebo-default-devel-precise-amd64/gazebo/test/ServerFixture.hh:136: Failure
69: Expected: (waitCount) < (maxWaitCount), actual: 3000 vs 3000
~~~

I added this timeout in pull request #211 while fixing issue #334. I had intended for the test to abort if the server didn't initialize, but the test keeps running until the 240 second timeout kicks in (see full console output below)

This may just be a ServerFixture problem, but we'll have to trap one of these failures before we can figure it out. Maybe we can add more debugging print statements near ServerFixture:136 if a failure occurs:
~~~
if (waitCount >= maxWaitCount)
{
  gzerr << "this->server " << this->server << "  "
        << "this->server->GetInitialized() " << this->server->GetInitialized() << "  "
        << "other relevant stuff...\n";
}
~~~
